to the Colonels' house for the radio.

1578
02:23:48.245 --> 02:23:49.538 line:82%
Do you really have to go?

1579
02:23:52.249 --> 02:23:53.709 line:82%
Just this last bit of work.

1580
02:23:56.211 --> 02:23:59.798 line:82%
Dad takes a while to get ready.
He will be down soon.

1581
02:24:00.257 --> 02:24:01.759 line:82%
-Dad!
-Rehan!

1582
02:24:13.228 --> 02:24:17.191 line:82%
Once upon a time, there was a prince,
and a princess who was blind.

1583
02:24:17.399 --> 02:24:19.234 line:82%
Mom, you are telling a story?

1584
02:24:21.612 --> 02:24:24.573 line:82%
One day the princess met an ordinary man

1585
02:24:24.698 --> 02:24:28.327 line:82%
who followed different monuments
in different cities.

1586
02:24:29.703 --> 02:24:33.707 line:82%
But the princess saw the prince hidden
in that ordinary man.

1587
02:24:34.458 --> 02:24:36.418 line:82%
What was the prince's name?

1588
02:24:37.127 --> 02:24:38.253 line:82%
Rehan.

1589
02:24:47.971 --> 02:24:51.934 line:82%
The prince saved the princess
from a huge, scary dragon.

1590
02:24:52.935 --> 02:24:56.063 line:82%
The dragon had a big, red face.

1591
02:24:56.146 --> 02:24:57.981 line:82%
Every time he opened his mouth,

1592
02:24:58.065 --> 02:25:00.651 line:82%
gigantic balls of fire
